\b0\fs22 Version 1.4.0.0 of PatchCleaner implements new functionality, including:\par
\par
\b\i File Details\b0\i0\par
PatchCleaner now provides the details of:\par

\pard\li720 1. The files that are still in use and need to be retained\par
2. The orphaned files including those files that are excluded via the exclusion filters\par

\pard\par
\b\i Exclusion filters\b0\i0  \par
There is a known issue in previous versions where PatchCleaner falsely identifies Adobe Acrobat Reader patches as not being required. Adobe do something proprietary when it comes to their automatic updating such that if PatchCleaner removes the "orphaned" patches from the installer directory, Adobe Reader automatic updates will no longer successfully install. \par
\par
The exclusion filters feature allows you to add keywords that are used in "contains" filters to exclude patches that match these keywords. These "contains" checks are applied against the file title, subject, author and digital signature.\par
\par
PatchCleaner is now pre-configured to exclude "Acrobat" which will exclude any Adobe Reader files from the set of orphaned files.\par
\par
These exclusion filters are able to altered by you.\par
\par
\b\i Bug Fixes\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\b0\i0 Issue with the "version" checking where version 1.3.0.0 always displayed that version 1.3.0.0 was available for download.\par

\pard\par
\b\i Adobe Reader\par
\b0\i0 If you are concerned that PatchCleaner has detected your AdobeReader patches as orphaned, you could apply the following steps to recover them. (Note: This assumes you have used the move feature and have access to the full list of patches that have been marked as orphaned.)\par
\par

\pard 
{\pntext\f0 1.\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec{\pntxta.}}
\fi-360\li720 Install PatchCleaner 1.4.0.0\par
{\pntext\f0 2.\tab}Run patch cleaner\par
{\pntext\f0 3.\tab}Move your orphaned files to your "Move" folder. Patch cleaner should now say you have "0" orphaned files.\par
{\pntext\f0 4.\tab}Copy your patches from your "Move" location back to "c:\\windows\\installer"\par
{\pntext\f0 5.\tab}Run PatchCleaner (or click refresh if you left it running)\par
{\pntext\f0 6.\tab}Use the delete action.\par

\pard\par
Any Adobe Reader patches that were copied back to "c:\\windows\\installer" as part of step 4, will have been excluded from the set of orphaned files and will remain in the installer folder.\par
\b\fs28\par
\fs24 Version 1.3.0.0 (Nov 2015)\par
